---
title: "Floor — Architecture Health Check (8-Step Process)"
---
flowchart TD
    START([Task Counter ≥ 10 triggers<br/>arch check instead of task prompt]) --> ENTRY

    ENTRY[User pastes arch check<br/>prompt into new session]

    %% ── Step 1 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    ENTRY --> S1[Step 1 — Read Standards]
    S1 --> S1_READ[Read architecture.md<br/>+ architecture-baseline.md]
    S1_READ --> S1_BASELINE{Baseline<br/>exists?}
    S1_BASELINE -->|Yes| S2
    S1_BASELINE -->|No| S1_FIRST[Note: this run produces<br/>initial baseline.<br/>Skip comparison in Step 6.]
    S1_FIRST --> S2

    %% ── Step 2 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    S2[Step 2 — Map Current Architecture]
    S2 --> S2_READ[Read every source file.<br/>For each, record:]
    S2_READ --> S2_DATA["• All import statements<br/>• Shared resource access<br/>• State mutations<br/>• Approximate line count"]

    %% ── Step 3 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    S2_DATA --> S3[Step 3 — Generate Current Diagram]
    S3 --> S3_MERMAID[Produce Mermaid dependency graph<br/>matching baseline format]
    S3_MERMAID --> S3_TABLE[Update Module Summary table]

    %% ── Step 4 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    S3_TABLE --> S4[Step 4 — Run Forbidden Pattern Checks]
    S4 --> S4_CHECKS["Execute F1–F4 check commands<br/>Execute F5: review import graph for cycles"]
    S4_CHECKS --> S4_RESULTS[Record pass/fail for each]

    %% ── Step 5 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    S4_RESULTS --> S5[Step 5 — Run Build & Lint]
    S5 --> S5_RUN[Run lint command + build command]
    S5_RUN --> S5_REPORT[Report errors/warnings]

    %% ── Step 6 ───────────────────────────────────────────
    S5_REPORT --> S6{Baseline<br/>exists?}
    S6 -->|No| S6_SKIP[Step 6 — Skipped<br/>Initial run, no comparison]
    S6 -->|Yes| S6_COMPARE[Step 6 — Compare to Baseline]

    S6_COMPARE --> S6_DIFF["Flag:<br/>• New dependencies<br/>• Removed dependencies<br/>• New/removed modules<br/>• Upward imports (layer violations)<br/>• Responsibility shifts"]

    %% ── Step 7 — Verdict ─────────────────────────────────
    S6_SKIP --> S7
    S6_DIFF --> S7

    S7{Step 7 — Verdict}

    S7 -->|No violations,<br/>no structural changes| PASS[PASS<br/>Architecture matches conventions.<br/>Update baseline date.]

    S7 -->|No violations,<br/>but new dependencies or<br/>structural changes that<br/>conform to conventions| PASS_NOTES["PASS WITH NOTES<br/>List intentional changes.<br/>Update baseline to reflect them."]

    S7 -->|One or more<br/>violations found| FAIL["FAIL<br/>List each violation:<br/>• Rule broken (F-number)<br/>• File and line<br/>• Suggested fix"]

    %% ── Step 8 — Baseline update ─────────────────────────
    PASS --> S8[Step 8 — Update Baseline]
    PASS_NOTES --> S8

    S8 --> S8_WRITE[Overwrite architecture-baseline.md<br/>with current diagram +<br/>updated Module Summary]
    S8_WRITE --> S8_DATE[Set Generated date to today]

    S8_DATE --> S8_NOTES{Pass with notes?}
    S8_NOTES -->|Yes| S8_RATIFIED[Add Ratified Changes section<br/>listing what changed and why]
    S8_NOTES -->|No| RESET_COUNTER

    S8_RATIFIED --> RESET_COUNTER

    FAIL --> NO_UPDATE[Do NOT update baseline]
    NO_UPDATE --> FAIL_ACTION[Agent presents violations.<br/>User decides next steps.]
    FAIL_ACTION --> FAIL_END([Flow ends — user must<br/>fix violations before<br/>next task prompt])

    RESET_COUNTER[Reset Task Counter<br/>in status.md to 0]
    RESET_COUNTER --> DONE([Arch check complete.<br/>User may now request<br/>next task.])

    %% ── Implicit failures ────────────────────────────────
    S4_CHECKS -.->|IMPLICIT FAILURE:<br/>F1-F4 check commands<br/>are project-specific<br/>placeholders until setup| S4_FAIL[If setup.md wasn't<br/>completed, checks are no-ops]

    S2_READ -.->|IMPLICIT FAILURE:<br/>LLM must manually read<br/>every source file —<br/>may miss files in<br/>large codebases| S2_FAIL[Incomplete mapping.<br/>Could be scripted<br/>with AST parsing.]

    RESET_COUNTER -.->|⚠ MIGRATION CANDIDATE:<br/>Counter reset is<br/>text editing by LLM| COUNTER_SCRIPT[Should be a script:<br/>python reset_task_counter.py]

    style S4_FAIL fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff
    style S2_FAIL fill:#f39c12,color:#fff
    style COUNTER_SCRIPT fill:#e67e22,color:#fff
    style FAIL fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff
    style PASS fill:#27ae60,color:#fff
    style PASS_NOTES fill:#f39c12,color:#fff
